value.0: This middle aged woman is the Three Roaring Winds long serving barkeeper, her eyes the ones of a woman who has seen the whole width of the sort of things one might expect to ocurr in a far out freezing island.
Hlif is one of the small handful of prostitutes working at the Three Roaring Winds, her smile is captivating and friendly, whether acted or not, who can really tell?

A fine stringed instrument, a lute is very mobile, and as such, a favorite of traveling minstrels everywhere.  It has a pleasing sound, as the strings musical vibrations echo in the hollow wooden chamber and reverberate.
A percussion instrument, the tambourine is a colorful and playful musical device that is often used in dancing and keeping a rhythm.
Clothing designed for forest dwellers and nature lovers alike, by Arwen E'lyn.

This gown has been cleverly dyed with fern patterns pressed down upon the skirt during the dying process.  This adds beauty and the helpful ability to hide among ferns if necessary!  Included are a pair of open-toed shoes.
This is armor, emblazoned with a Cordorian insignia, is issued to the greenest members of the Cordorian Guard Adventuring Unit.
This magic weapon has an enhancement bonus to attack and damage, but it doesn't bear the hallmarks of any specific maker.

This set of mail is often found in the company of barbarians, as it fits well to the bearer without hampering movement severely.  It also has a slight effect of intimidation by this association as well.  This particular armor was forged to protect it's wearer from goblinoids.

It is a simple chair but the grace of its lines speaks to the quality of its craftmanship.
This rug is beautifully woven, with intricate patterns that draw you in more the closer you look.
Lowland's Red Lager, a perfect beer for a warm summer evening with friends.
Beverage: Ole Griff's Finest Red Lager
Riverwest Pale Ale, brewed in small batches by Bill Jordan at Mayfield's.
Riverwest Pale Ale, brewed in small batches by Bill Jordan at Mayfield's.

Freshly squeezed daily from the outlying farms, Griff eventually succumbed to stocking this by request of Gabriel Judicator.

Milk.  It does a body good.
Another beverage requested by the elven patrons, mead is a fast selling beverage at the Nomad.  It's taste usually an acquired one, it is usually ordered by customers who know what they like.

This milk has a distinct chocolatey flavor, which is highly prized by youngsters that find themselves in the Nomad.   Brewed in small batches, this novelty very well may hit it big in Cordor after all....

Milk.  It does a body good.

Sweetberry juice - a simple drink made of wine mixed with sweetberry powder, giving it a kick but a pleasant sweet after-taste. Ordered by the Nomad after many personal requests from a particular customer.

Created by the Gnome Giggledunk Gnafflepot to make sure that drinks can be both drinkable and eatable. As you shake the bottle containing the liquid, the liquid will start transforming into a Jelly of sorts, which you easily can poor from the bottle and, later on, eat with a spoon. This transformation neutralizes the alcohol and creates a sugary and sweet Jelly, enjoyed greatly by many. 
The drinkable part is sweet, with a hint of sugar. It can be served on almost any occasion and it is most enjoyable ice-cold.

Created by the Gnome Giggledunk Gnafflepot to make sure that drinks can be both drinkable and eatable. As you shake the bottle containing the liquid, the liquid will start transforming into a Jelly of sorts, which you easily can poor from the bottle and, later on, eat with a spoon. This transformation magically neutralizes the alcohol and creates a bitter and thick Jelly, also eatable with a spoon. This drink is favored by many, mostly Hins and the ones with Orc blood running through their veins. 
The drinkable part is like the Jelly, bitter, swampy but also quite strong.

When you peek in the tea cup a fuschia tea froths within, a few glossy, blackish purple berries float on the top. Mmm, tart but suprisingly delicious - it tastes a little like mangos! It surely gets your heart pumping, in fact...you feel a little hot, even your mouth seems a little dry. All the more reason to drink the rest!

(Note: Belladonna is a mildly poisonus plant which include symptoms of belladonna poisoning include high fever, rapid pulse, dilation of pupils, hot and dry flushed skin, headache, dry mouth, difficulty swallowing, burning of the throat, hallucinations, and convulsions. DC 13 Fort Save may be necessary if you have heart troubles or high blood pressure.)
This hot and bitter drink comes with a slice of lemon the rim. When drunk, it has a hint of spice, milk, and...mint? This will surely get your senses buzzing, though your taste buds may question it.
This blend of citrus juices is mixed and sweetened to just the right taste.
Served steaming hot and with whipped cream on the top, this rich chocolate drink is a favorite of adults and children alike.
Iced tea, served sweet and cold. Complete with a side of lemon.
Potions store various spells, both beneficial and otherwise, until consumed.

This concoction is made by crushing a Sweetberry into a fine powder. Normally, the result is a powder that control those of weak will. But, when mixing this fine powder into milk, it creates a tangy drink, that can be used as a great relaxing agent. 

Created by Naliss Phrozenflare.
Bill tells you to go easy on this stuff....  "It'll make yer tempers flare, youngblood!!" he says.  You had better heed Bill's warning.

Pours a clear reddish amber with a frothy, foamy head that settles into a thin sudsy lacing. It has aromas of lightly toasted grains, a apple and grape fruitiness with a little orange zest, earthy yeast, and a soft floral hoppiness. 

Pleasant tasting, toasted grassy grains and caramelized sugary maltiness, earthy, peppery yeastiness, a light fruitiness, a bit apple and orange, spicy hops with a soft, but lingering bitterness, a slight taste of alcohol towards the end, the alcohol provides a subtle warming in the palate, and a dry grainy, subtle fruity, spicy finish.
Lowland's Red Lager, a perfect beer for a warm summer evening with friends.
Beverage: Ole Griff's Finest Red Lager

Once the nitro pour storm settles down, the beer is a nice thick brown-black, topped by a thick and creamy head of tan foam. Great head retention and spotty lacing. A tangy and roasted malt aroma is quite noticeable. Smooth and dry roasted malt flavor, with a touch of black coffee in there too. Medium bodied, quite mellow. Delicious when the mood strikes.

Brewed for generations, this ale is made using a secret family recipe that will be defended to the death...probably yours.  Odd, the strange afterbite, though...I wonder what that extra ingredient is..
A piece of Jerky, cooked and dried to absolute perfection.
There are many unusual items in the game. This is one of them.
This freshly baked muffin is quite a treat. Warm and flaky, with freshly picked blueberries baked into it, it dares you to eat just one.

This water is guarenteed! Bottled fresh daily from Nexus Falls. It tastes just the same as any other water but, costs tons more. No one wants to drink water from a glass when you can have it from a bottle instead!

An original idea from a small elven girl, this snack consists of little shreds of white bread, rolled tightly into a ball with a sprinkled sugar coating. This treat can surely provide a quick solution to the days problems.

This cookie appears to have been from a burnt batch; a blackened wing has crumbled off to reveal it's charred ingredients, though this has been hastily covered up with a good portion of icing.

Though when you bite into it, you get the feeling the taste isn't the only thing that has been altered.

Another creation famed to a small elven lass, this sandwich delights in three different tastes: old, cheesy and spicey - all at the same time! Though that may not be a good thing. 
Eating this would give you really bad breath...and perhaps ward off your friends.
These whole wheat crackers are salted and have a light buttery taste to them. Coming in small packets of 10, they're a perfect snack for people on the go.

Hey, it's a hot, batter coated piece of...something. You're not quite sure what, but it smells kinda good.

Although, biting into it may have it's side effects.

This fruit salad is made from some of the sweetest fruits found on the island. Some warn that eating too much of this can send your brain into a sort of sugar shock, and you will begin to see things that aren't actually there... or are they?
There are many unusual items in the game. This is one of them.
Aw, it's shaped like a gargoyle! It even has frosting and raspberries for eyes, a snack that'll bring to delight to anyone's eyes.
A taste of these magically enhanced mint leaves will leave you're mouth on fire. After something that strong, surely you'll be able to resist anything.
There are many unusual items in the game. This is one of them.

Wisps of yellow-orange translucent soup seem to be floating within this tiny bowl - it tastes oddly like chicken noodle. This doesn't seem to fill you up much, and the more you eat, the harder it is to hold the spoon.

Is it breakfast? Is it lunch? Is it dinner? Is it an appetizer, or a main course? Depending upon who you ask in the beautiful metropolis of Cordor, you'll receive a different story. Some say this dubiously hearty pastry of eggs, baked cheese, rich buttercream, bacon bits, and freshly diced onions is the greatest culinary innovation ever concocted in Toril. Others claim that real men just don't eat quiche. But there is one thing that everyone can agree on about this delicious dish: "Its simply divine!"

It is the destiny of the drow to conquer, on all fronts, and the café scene is no different. Not one to be outdone by surfacer kitchen talent, the dangerous denizens of the Underdark supposedly created their own varation on the quiche recipe. Baked from the crushed bones of kidnapped surface victims, filled with the tangy filling of flayed infant flesh, and smeared with a slightly bitter glaze of various arachnid venoms, Quiche Ultrinnan is a dish intended to please the palate of select clientele. The ingredients are obviously just clever and seditious marketing, but politically conscientous diners jeer the recipe for being advertised in poor taste. The popularity of this dish, however, would suggest that it actually tastes pretty good.

Following the successful debut of Quiche Cordor into the Amian fine dining scene, an order of Verdant Chefs from the elven city of Winya turned up their noses at the uncouth ingredients of butchered pig and decadent buttercream, and replaced them with a more wholesome, organic spinach and nut oil combination, and used a leaner variety of cheese with a lower calorie count and a higher nutritional value. "Its important for us to stay in touch with the land that gave birth to the bounty we eat," one of the chefs is quoted as saying. "And real men may not eat quiche, but the elves of Winya certainly do, thank you very much."
This small, fruity cake is often enjoyed by the more upper-class of Cordorians. It's served with a choice of jam, butter and cream, or for the particularly adventurous, all three at the same time.

A slighlty grayish liquid foams and bubbles within the metal cup - it seems to be quickly eating away at it's container. It smells a little like tea, looks like acid, but tastes suprisingly mild and unharmful. In fact, it gives you a nice warm and hardy feeling inside.

Careful not to spill - you might do more than just stian your clothes.
A mixture of nuts, dried fruits, and seeds. This trail mix is an adventurer's favorite treat.
There are many unusual items in the game. This is one of them.
